
                                                             short-site-name


    FUNCTION
    short-site-name  -  get the short name of the physical location of your
      hardware

    Usage
    short-site-name

    DESCRIPTION
    Returns the string that identifies the shorter version of  the  name  of
    the  physical  location  of  the machine on which you are running COMMON
    LISP.  If the information is not available, nil is returned.   The  pre-
    cise string returned is implementation-dependent.

    EXAMPLES
    ;; The followinging result is implementation-dependent.
    (short-site-name) => "fridge.franzinc"

    SEE ALSO
    CLtL 25:448, long-site-name











































